{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ensure the income threshold for Pension Credit is higher than the State Pension",
        "additional_details": "This means many pensioners cannot claim Pension Credit because their State Pension is \u00a32.55 over the income threshold.\r\n \r\nMany pensioners cannot claim Pension Credit because they receive a full State Pension so are just over the threshold to be eligible for this benefit.\r\n \r\nThis means they miss out on:\r\n \r\nCold weather payments\r\nWarm Home Discount\r\nCost of Living payments\r\nFree glasses\r\nFree dental care\r\nFull Housing Benefit and Council Tax discount\r\nFree TV licence\r\n \r\nThis is grossly unfair when they are just \u00a32.55 above the threshold to claim and are struggling to make ends meet.\r\n",
        "background": "Currently the single person income threshold for Pension Credit is \u00a3182.60 a week, but the new State Pension is \u00a3185.15 per week.",
